    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Alchemy Manual pg. 21</em>, <em>Elves of Golarion pg. 23</em><br /><strong>Price</strong> 100 gp; <strong>Weight</strong> -<br /><strong>Category</strong> Alchemical Weapons</p>\n<h2 class=\"framing\">Description</h2>\n<p>Behind the head of this arrow is a small receptacle of alchemical material that heats up when exposed to air and eventually combusts; barbs on the arrowhead pierce the pouch when it hits a target.</p>\n<p>If you hit a target with a slow burn arrow, it deals damage as normal, but at the beginning of your next turn, the arrow bursts into flames and deals <strong>1d6 points of fire damage</strong> to the target.</p>\n<h2 class=\"framing\">Alchemical Recipe</h2>\n<p><strong>Recipe</strong> (70 magnesium + 80 myrrh + 25 phosphorus)/congelation; <strong>Craft</strong> 25<br /><strong>Time</strong> 10 minutes; <strong>Tools</strong> alchemist's lab; <strong>Type</strong> alchemical weapon</p>",
